00:39:27,800 --> 00:39:30,420
<i>All the molecules</i> <i>appear to be the same.</i>

486
00:39:30,490 --> 00:39:33,790
<i>Yes.</i> <i>Andromeda isn't composed</i> <i>of different substances...</i>

487
00:39:33,850 --> 00:39:35,740
<i>like a normal cell.</i>

488
00:39:35,800 --> 00:39:37,870
All the subunits are the same.

489
00:39:37,950 --> 00:39:42,140
Damndest thing I've ever s... Boy, a single substance.

490
00:39:42,200 --> 00:39:44,540
<i>Then how the hell</i> <i>does it operate?</i>

491
00:39:44,600 --> 00:39:47,730
<i>How does anything so simple</i> <i>utilize energy for growth?</i>

492
00:39:47,800 --> 00:39:49,740
<i>No way of telling</i> <i>from that structure.</i>

493
00:39:49,820 --> 00:39:52,020
Yes, there is. With this new data,

494
00:39:52,090 --> 00:39:55,540
